Rating: 3
These were tasty and looked great on my cookie platter. I used other reviewers suggestion of adding a couple extra tablespoons of butter to make the dough a little easier to handle. In the end they were beautiful but I can certainly see how this dough could be a bit tricky right out of the fridge. It helps to let them warm up before attempting to roll. Even the cracks in the dough were easily smoothed out on the baking sheet.

Rating: 4
This is one the favorite cookies at our house and is very yummy! I make the recipe as written, except our resident cookie monster doesn't like walnuts. So I leave them out. Have never had a problem with the dough being too dry. I do slice them more thinly sometimes though. They are very pretty and a lot of fun to make.

Rating: 4
I made the recipe exactly as it was written and the cookies came out delicious. These cookies are a family favorite.

