Rating: 3
I followed another reviewers suggestion and added an extra 1/4 cup of butter when I was making the cokies. The dough wasn't to dry and I liked the end result.

Rating: 2
I agree with the previous reviewers, I made recipe as is and the dough for these cookies was too dry. I have a similar shortbread type dough recipe that calls for double the butter in this recipe for the same amount of flour. I will make this recipe again, but I would try it with at least another 1/4 cup of butter, and maybe unsweetened coconut to make it a little less sweet. And these cookies don't flatten out at all when they're baked, I'd slice them 1/4 inch thick instead of 1/2.

Rating: 1
There is a MUCH better cookie recipe on this web site -- Oatmeal Coconut Raspberry Bars -- that has the same flavor and is easier to bake and serve. Try that recipe instead to save time and aggravation.

Rating: 1
These cookies were a bust--literally. The dough seemed suspiciously dry from the get-go, and when I tried to roll it, it just crumbled to pieces. With nothing else for my Valentine :8(, I shoveled up the pieces, placed them in a baking dish, baked for 20 minutes at 375. It came out very tasty, if not very presentable--but this is SWEET. Whipped cream helped cut the sugar.